title: Farm value per liter of maple syrup in Ontario 2000 to 2018
yAxis: Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars
summary: Overall Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars has increased over the Year.
Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars is roughly constant from 2004 to 2006, and finally slightly increasing from 2006 to 2008.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2007 and 2008.
Maximum Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars, about 12.99 was reported at Year 2008
The lowest Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars, of value 11.03 was reported at Year 2004
